</b>124.115 <b>Align its criminal justice system with its obligations under the ICCPR 
and other international human rights instruments (Australia); 
</b>124.116 <b>Create a national mechanism for the review of complaints of the 
populations concerning human rights violations (Russian Federation); 
</b>124.117 <b>Make efforts to achieve respect for all fundamental rights and 
freedoms of the entire population, especially women and children, and take all 
necessary measures to ensure the fight against impunity for the perpetrators of 
crimes, acts of violence and all human rights violations (Argentina); 
</b>124.118 <b>Take all necessary measures to prevent or punish violations of human 
rights (Burundi); 
</b>124.119 <b>Tackle impunity by investigating and timely prosecuting those 
